1
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,200
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,360
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
[Episode 8]

23
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:35,800
[[Customs Dormitory]]

24
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:41,460
I don't get it.
I just wanted to help people.

25
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:44,820
I wasn't trying to play hero
or show off.

26
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:47,340
I was doing the right thing.

27
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:48,820
But to him,

28
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:50,860
none of that mattered.

29
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,700
All he saw

30
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:55,540
was me crossing the line,

31
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:58,140
going off script,
and breaking the rules.

32
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,540
So what does that make me?

33
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:03,220
And the things I wanted to do…
What are they worth?

34
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:06,340
Focus on what's in front of you.

35
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:07,420
Anything beyond that

36
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:08,340
isn't your job.

37
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:13,020
Are you sure you're in the right place?

38
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,780
You should've been a detective.

39
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:19,180
So working at Customs

40
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:22,100
just means standing at the gate
and watching?

41
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:06,100
Didn't sleep much, huh?

42
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:08,420
I was a bit hard on you last night.

43
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,700
But taking time to think it through

44
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:11,820
isn't a bad thing.

45
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:15,820
Better to sort it out now

46
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,740
than crash later.

47
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,860
Back then, I was the same.

48
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,220
I thought about it.

49
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:24,420
I'm not cut out
for Passenger Inspection.

50
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,780
You thought all night,

51
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:30,260
and this is your answer? Running away?

52
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,180
I joined Customs

53
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:34,980
to go after smugglers.

54
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:38,180
Not to stand at the counter
every day, checking bags

55
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:39,180
and keeping order.

56
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:40,620
If I can't make arrests,

57
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:42,100
there's no point in me staying.

58
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,340
I want to do something that matters.

59
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,340
What's going on?

60
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,300
So in your mind,

61
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:10,180
a Customs officer

62
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,820
should be a dark knight,

63
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,420
a lone hero,

64
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:17,540
going head-to-head

65
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:18,900
with smugglers.

66
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:19,460
Is that it?

67
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,140
Don't you think that's unprofessional?

68
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,580
What's wrong with that?

69
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:30,820
I wanted to join
the anti-smuggling unit.

70
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:32,060
Not Passenger Inspection.

71
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,220
If it weren't for my eyesight…

72
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:43,260
So there's a history, too.

73
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:46,340
Fine.

74
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,540
You wouldn't make it
into anti-smuggling.

75
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:54,100
And even if you did,

76
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,900
you still wouldn't make
a good anti-smuggling officer.

77
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,500
If I'd known about this,

78
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:01,580
Section I wouldn't have taken you.

79
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,820
Because you have

80
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:07,260
no sense of duty or mission

81
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:08,140
as a Customs officer.

82
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:09,180
None.

83
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:12,100
I'm talking about Customs as a whole.

84
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:15,500
Anti-smuggling and Passenger Inspection
are two lines of defense for Customs.

85
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,380
And either one

86
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,700
depends on teamwork!

87
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:21,260
But you?

88
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,420
You're full of

89
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:25,460
personal heroism.

90
00:05:25,960 --> 00:05:27,220
You do things your own way

91
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:30,180
and ignore the team behind you.

92
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:32,180
You completely ignore

93
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,020
team discipline!

94
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,060
Zhang Yu, listen.

95
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:40,380
Every job, every role,

96
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:42,740
has its own rules.

97
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,740
Even a game has rules.

98
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,660
If you don't respect them,

99
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:49,380
your teammates pay the price.

100
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,820
Have you thought about that?

101
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:58,820
Of course not.

102
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:04,100
This resignation letter
shows you don't care.

103
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:06,740
Zhang Yu,

104
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:10,460
at least you're self-aware.

105
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,420
You did come to the wrong place.

106
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:19,260
Mr. Guo,

107
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:19,740
I'm not…

108
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:21,140
I'll submit this resignation letter

109
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:22,820
to Mr. Shen ASAP.

110
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:28,660
I'm informing you now.

111
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,940
From now on,

112
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:33,100
you're on internal duty.

113
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,220
Take a few days off and reflect.

114
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:37,620
I'll report this to headquarters.

115
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,500
Thank you, Mr. Guo.

116
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:42,940
Put your hand down!

117
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:50,060
Don't salute me.

118
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:54,020
I won't accept it.

119
00:08:07,080 --> 00:08:08,760
[Binhai Aviation Catering Company]

120
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:12,220
Mentor.

121
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,340
Listen up.

122
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:18,660
No one bothers Zhang Yu
for the next few days.

123
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,100
Let her be alone.

124
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,260
She's got her own issues

125
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,540
she needs to figure out.

126
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:26,260
You focus on yourselves.

127
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:27,020
Don't make things worse.

128
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:28,780
Got it?

129
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:29,700
Got it.

130
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:31,700
Don't end up

131
00:08:32,030 --> 00:08:33,380
making things harder for Zhang Yu.

132
00:08:33,790 --> 00:08:35,420
Your mentors know what they're doing.

133
00:08:35,550 --> 00:08:36,260
Then

134
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,940
can we bring her something to eat?

135
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,060
No.

136
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:41,380
Anyone who does will be written up.

137
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:50,820
I thought if I stopped,

138
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,060
I'd feel lighter.

139
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:53,900
But it's not like that at all.

140
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,220
The moment I slowed down,

141
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:58,620
everything just felt empty.

142
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,060
I still think I wasn't wrong.

143
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,540
But his words

144
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,740
keep echoing in my head.

145
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:09,980
Is Passenger Inspection
really what I thought it was?

146
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:22,100
Watching them work from a distance,

147
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:24,740
watching passenger inspection
run as usual,

148
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,580
watching all those things
I used to think

149
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,180
were repetitive and trivial

150
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:30,060
happen one after another…

151
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:34,500
They were still there, as always,
standing at their posts,

152
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:37,140
calm and sure of themselves.

153
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:47,660
What are you doing here?

154
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:49,220
I…

155
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,420
Don't mind me.

156
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:55,420
It's like only by standing here
and watching them

157
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:59,100
can I start to untangle

158
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:02,140
the mess in my head.

159
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:04,580
But even then,

160
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,740
it's still too unclear.

161
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:12,060
She's got real potential.
You're just going to let her go?

162
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,380
Her heart's not in it.

163
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:16,860
Not so sure.

164
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:18,180
If she wanted out,

165
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,660
she wouldn't keep showing up.

166
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:21,460
She doesn't want to quit.

167
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:23,220
She just needs time.

168
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:25,060
We should help her.

169
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,580
You've got an idea?

170
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:29,180
Take her to Xishan.

171
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,180
One trip to Xishan's gonna
change her mind?

172
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,740
Xishan's just a way in.

173
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:34,860
She won't really quit.

174
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:35,980
Fine. You take her.

175
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:36,820
I'm not going.

176
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,060
It's your idea.

177
00:10:57,880 --> 00:10:58,940
You slept here?

178
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:03,300
Deng.

179
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:05,380
Get up. Now.

180
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:07,260
Someone's here for you.

181
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:09,300
Who?

182
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:10,820
Go see for yourself.

183
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:16,020
Hurry up.

184
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,700
What's that?

185
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:22,820
On your back.

186
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,540
You really know how to make me worry.

187
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:49,900
Oh, it's you. Shihuo.

188
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:54,580
Could you at least hide
that disappointed look?

189
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:55,740
No,

190
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:56,460
I…

191
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:57,660
Isn't that my mentor's…

192
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:00,700
Isn't this Mr. Guo's car?

193
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,220
What are you doing here?

194
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,260
I need you

195
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:05,380
to be my driver for the day.

196
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:05,900
Would that be okay?

197
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:07,700
I can't drive.

198
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:09,900
Sure.

199
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:11,620
But why me?

200
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,420
Because you've got time.

201
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,220
Fair point.

202
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:16,260
So,

203
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:18,500
Mr. Guo brought you here?

204
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:20,260
No, Deng did.

205
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:20,660
Here.

206
00:12:22,880 --> 00:12:23,220
Let's go.

207
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:25,420
Come on.

208
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:35,860
Take a left at the next intersection
and merge onto the main road.

209
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,820
Where are we going?

210
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:42,500
Taking you to pick oranges.

211
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:56,740
Sir,

212
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:59,740
these orah mandarins look great.

213
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:01,620
Have you been growing them for years?

214
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:03,020
Not really.

215
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:06,660
Just a few years.

216
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:09,020
We've got good land here.

217
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:11,020
The water, the soil,

218
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,380
the air,

219
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:14,060
the humidity, the temperature…

220
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:15,980
All perfect for fruit trees.

221
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,220
Yeah, you're really blessed.

222
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:19,900
Not quite.

223
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,980
Things have only gotten better
these past few years.

224
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,420
A few years back,

225
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:25,340
some people

226
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:28,060
came around selling citrus saplings.

227
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:30,060
They said they'd produce well,

228
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,500
bring in good money,

229
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:32,660
and were top-quality stock.

230
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:34,500
Talked a big game.

231
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,220
Everyone believed them,

232
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:38,660
so every household planted some.

233
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:40,540
But

234
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:42,500
when harvest came,

235
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:43,900
forget the citrus,

236
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,620
even the nearby fruit

237
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,020
all rotted.

238
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,620
Could it have been the saplings?

239
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:51,700
Exactly.

240
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:54,100
That's where it went wrong.

241
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,140
But back then,

242
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,380
we didn't know what to do.

243
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,140
Those people even said

244
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,180
we planted them wrong.

245
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,620
So how did you fix it?

246
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:06,860
Eventually,

247
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:08,180
it got fixed.

248
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,980
Customs helped us.

249
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:14,580
Customs?

250
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:15,220
Yeah.

251
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:16,460
Binhai Customs?

252
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:17,340
Right.

253
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,220
Huayan Airport Customs.

254
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,660
Airport Customs?

255
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:25,220
The ones who sold us those saplings…

256
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:27,980
they were heartless.

257
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:30,260
Every tree they sold us

258
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:33,180
was infected with citrus black spot.

259
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:35,500
We worked hard all year,

260
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:38,180
only to watch our fruit rot
in the fields.

261
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:39,740
Luckily,

262
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,100
someone in our village

263
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,860
knew Director Chen from Customs.

264
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:45,100
When he heard what had happened,

265
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:48,140
he brought a team of experts
straight to the village.

266
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,860
They went door to door,

267
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,380
teaching us

268
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,940
how to deal with the disease

269
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:54,300
and helping us

270
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,700
restore the whole orchard.

271
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,300
I remember it clearly.

272
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,460
There was this young guy,

273
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:04,820
handsome,

274
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,460
really capable,

275
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:07,580
and sharp as a tack.

276
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,260
Thanks to them,

277
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:11,940
our orchards recovered.

278
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:15,100
Later, the government
allocated us this land.

279
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:17,340
Now we grow citrus

280
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:18,260
and orah mandarins.

281
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:20,060
Life's been getting better every year.

282
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:23,060
Thinking about it now,

283
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:24,700
all these years,

284
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:28,380
I've wanted to thank
the Customs officers.

285
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:29,980
Just never got the chance.

286
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:34,220
Sir,

287
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:38,740
the handsome guy you mentioned…
was it him?

288
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,060
